cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.SY

This paper deals with the connectivity of device-to-device networks in an urban scenario, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses percolation theory and simulations to analyze the network, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper uses a mathematical model to represent the network, which is related to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also discusses the impact of network parameters on connectivity, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
